<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>As of late there has been a resurgence of the old and vintage becoming new once again. That can well be said for the flame stitch pattern. This centuries-old pattern returns with a playful yet sophisticated transformation. From transitional to contemporary and don't forget eclectic, the flame stitch brings a sense of life and whimsy to any interior design. </p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<div align="center" class="row">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<a href="http://erikabrechtel.com/2012/04/24/interview-designer-gabriel-hendifar/" target="_blank">
